claim.claim-text:
10. The method of claim 9, wherein:
X is a respective target lower limit or a nominal upper limit on an average amount of data transmitted per timeslot between the hub and the pertinent remote terminal;
X is the lower limit if the current token count for the pertinent remote terminal has a positive value;
X is the nominal upper limit if said count has a negative value; and
the nominal upper limit is set so high that it does not effectively limit said average amount of data.
